Guide
https://thepihut.com/blogs/raspberry-pi-tutorials/16021420-how-to-install-use-the-raspberry-pi-camera



0. Install it manually
1. Must enable the camera ( sudo raspi-config ) It should be under interface options, you can navigate and enable it
2. After it was enabled, or even if it did not appeared, run:
  "sudo apt-get update" and then "sudo apt-get upgrade"
  
  Start Using it ! 
  
 ---- raspistill and raspivid  ---
  
  
To capture an image in jpeg format, type:

 "raspistill -o image.jpg" 
 
 at the prompt ( * where "image" is the name of your image ) 
  
  To capture video, we use raspivid ( We will not use it in our lab ) 
  
 To capture a 10 second video with your Raspberry Pi camera module, run "raspivid -o video.h264 -t 10000" at the prompt
 where "video" is the name of your video and "10000" is the number of milliseconds
 
  
   
